    "what_description": "Didymochlaena spinulosa is a species of fern in the family Polypodiaceae. It is a terrestrial fern with a rhizome that produces long, narrow fronds that are pinnate and have a lanceolate shape. The fronds are 10-35 cm long and 5-15 cm wide, with a rachis that is scaly and has black spines. The leaflets are 2-10 cm long and 1-3 cm wide, with a cuneate base and a serrate margin. The plant is native to tropical Africa and is characterized by its distinctive black spines on the rachis.",
