    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Didymochlaena spinulosa are infusion, decoction, tincture, tea, and salve, which are used to harness its medicinal properties. Infusion involves steeping the dried fronds in hot water to create a soothing tea, rich in vitamins and minerals, particularly iron, which is beneficial for anemia. Decoction of the root is used to treat various ailments, including fever and rheumatism, as it contains anti-inflammatory compounds like flavonoids and phenolic acids. Tincture of Didymochlaena spinulosa is prepared by soaking the dried plant material in a solvent, such as ethanol or glycerin, to create a concentrated liquid extract, which is used in traditional medicine to treat various health issues. The salve preparation involves mixing the herbal extract with a carrier oil, like coconut or olive oil, to create a topical treatment for skin conditions, including wounds and eczema.",
